{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778983353858,"sessionID":"ses_1cc55b36fffel5c7VxLvlJzw3W","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_wD8GvruwRZ9rQM7R8IknMyn6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/references_cache/PMID_19575650.md","offset":1,"limit":200},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/references_cache/PMID_19575650.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: reference_id: PMID:19575650\n3: title: Tethering factors as organizers of intracellular vesicular traffic.\n4: authors:\n5: - Yu IM\n6: - Hughson FM\n7: journal: Annu Rev Cell Dev Biol\n8: year: '2010'\n9: doi: 10.1146/annurev.cellbio.042308.113327\n10: keywords:\n11: - Animals\n12: - Multiprotein Complexes/metabolism\n13: - SNARE Proteins/metabolism\n14: - Transport Vesicles/metabolism\n15: - Vesicular Transport Proteins/metabolism\n16: content_type: abstract_only\n17: ---\n18: \n19: # Tethering factors as organizers of intracellular vesicular traffic.\n20: **Authors:** Yu IM, Hughson FM\n21: **Journal:** Annu Rev Cell Dev Biol (2010)\n22: **DOI:** [10.1146/annurev.cellbio.042308.113327](https://doi.org/10.1146/annurev.cellbio.042308.113327)\n23: \n24: ## Content\n25: \n26: 1. Annu Rev Cell Dev Biol. 2010;26:137-56. doi: \n27: 10.1146/annurev.cellbio.042308.113327.\n28: \n29: Tethering factors as organizers of intracellular vesicular traffic.\n30: \n31: Yu IM(1), Hughson FM.\n32: \n33: Author information:\n34: (1)Department of Molecular Biology, Princeton University, Princeton, New Jersey \n35: 08544, USA.\n36: \n37: Intracellular trafficking entails the budding, transport, tethering, and fusion \n38: of transport vesicles and other membrane carriers. Here we review recent \n39: progress toward a mechanistic understanding of vesicle tethering. The known \n40: tethering factors are large complexes important for one or more intracellular \n41: trafficking pathways and are capable of interacting directly with many of the \n42: other principal components of the cellular trafficking machinery. Our review \n43: emphasizes recent developments in the in vitro reconstitution of vesicle \n44: tethering and the structural characterization of multisubunit tethering factors. \n45: The combination of these and other approaches has led to exciting progress \n46: toward understanding how these essential nanomachines work.\n47: \n48: DOI: 10.1146/annurev.cellbio.042308.113327\n49: PMID: 19575650 [Indexed for MEDLINE]\n\n(End of file - total 49 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nreference_id: PMID:19575650\ntitle: Tethering factors as organizers of intracellular vesicular traffic.\nauthors:\n- Yu IM\n- Hughson FM\njournal: Annu Rev Cell Dev Biol\nyear: '2010'\ndoi: 10.1146/annurev.cellbio.042308.113327\nkeywords:\n- Animals\n- Multiprotein Complexes/metabolism\n- SNARE Proteins/metabolism\n- Transport Vesicles/metabolism\n- Vesicular Transport Proteins/metabolism\ncontent_type: abstract_only\n---\n\n# Tethering factors as organizers of intracellular vesicular traffic.\n**Authors:** Yu IM, Hughson FM","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"references_cache/PMID_19575650.md","time":{"start":1778983353847,"end":1778983353856}},"id":"prt_e33abbdf20011mKeTxWB1K0KFN","sessionID":"ses_1cc55b36fffel5c7VxLvlJzw3W","messageID":"msg_e33abaf810017HeNngcH0DZub3"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778983353886,"sessionID":"ses_1cc55b36fffel5c7VxLvlJzw3W","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_AtLR5ZeoxPOoLhz7zukaxGiY","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/references_cache/PMID_19887069.md","offset":1,"limit":200},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/references_cache/PMID_19887069.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: reference_id: PMID:19887069\n3: title: Role of vesicle tethering factors in the ER-Golgi membrane traffic.\n4: authors:\n5: - Sztul E\n6: - Lupashin V\n7: journal: FEBS Lett\n8: year: '2009'\n9: doi: 10.1016/j.febslet.2009.10.083\n10: keywords:\n11: - Animals\n12: - Biological Transport\n13: - Cytoplasmic Vesicles/metabolism\n14: - Endoplasmic Reticulum/metabolism\n15: - Golgi Apparatus/metabolism\n16: - Humans\n17: - Intracellular Membranes/metabolism\n18: content_type: abstract_only\n19: ---\n20: \n21: # Role of vesicle tethering factors in the ER-Golgi membrane traffic.\n22: **Authors:** Sztul E, Lupashin V\n23: **Journal:** FEBS Lett (2009)\n24: **DOI:** [10.1016/j.febslet.2009.10.083](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.febslet.2009.10.083)\n25: \n26: ## Content\n27: \n28: 1. FEBS Lett. 2009 Dec 3;583(23):3770-83. doi: 10.1016/j.febslet.2009.10.083.\n29: Epub  2009 Nov 1.\n30: \n31: Role of vesicle tethering factors in the ER-Golgi membrane traffic.\n32: \n33: Sztul E(1), Lupashin V.\n34: \n35: Author information:\n36: (1)Department of Cell Biology, University of Alabama at Birmingham, 1918 \n37: University Boulevard, Birmingham, AL 35294, USA.\n38: \n39: Tethers are a diverse group of loosely related proteins and protein complexes \n40: grouped into three families based on structural and functional similarities. A \n41: well-accepted role for tethering factors is the initial attachment of transport \n42: carriers to acceptor membranes prior to fusion. However, accumulating evidence \n43: indicates that tethers are more than static bridges. Tethers have been shown to \n44: interact with components of the fusion machinery and with components involved in \n45: vesicle formation. Tethers belonging to the three families act at the same stage \n46: of traffic, suggesting that they mediate distinct events during vesicle \n47: tethering. Thus, multiple tether-facilitated events are required to provide \n48: selectivity to vesicle fusion. In this review, we highlight findings that \n49: support this model.\n50: \n51: DOI: 10.1016/j.febslet.2009.10.083\n52: PMCID: PMC2788073\n53: PMID: 19887069 [Indexed for MEDLINE]\n\n(End of file - total 53 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nreference_id: PMID:19887069\ntitle: Role of vesicle tethering factors in the ER-Golgi membrane traffic.\nauthors:\n- Sztul E\n- Lupashin V\njournal: FEBS Lett\nyear: '2009'\ndoi: 10.1016/j.febslet.2009.10.083\nkeywords:\n- Animals\n- Biological Transport\n- Cytoplasmic Vesicles/metabolism\n- Endoplasmic Reticulum/metabolism\n- Golgi Apparatus/metabolism\n- Humans\n- Intracellular Membranes/metabolism\ncontent_type: abstract_only\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"references_cache/PMID_19887069.md","time":{"start":1778983353868,"end":1778983353884}},"id":"prt_e33abbdfa001v4kwu9RcPpLlhK","sessionID":"ses_1cc55b36fffel5c7VxLvlJzw3W","messageID":"msg_e33abaf810017HeNngcH0DZub3"}}
