{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778983585940,"sessionID":"ses_1cc55b36fffel5c7VxLvlJzw3W","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_giKKFggXGufHoJBYgRX7gdTS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_7770062.obo\n@@\n synonym: \"vesicle membrane tether activity\" EXACT []\n+synonym: \"vesicle membrane adaptor activity\" EXACT []\n synonym: \"vesicle tethering activity\" EXACT []\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+## Issue 31863 research summary\n+\n+The imported issue requested a new molecular function term, `vesicle membrane tethering activity`, supported by the ER-Golgi tethering review `PMID:19887069`, plus a broader review covering vesicular trafficking beyond that single pathway.\n+\n+## PMID:19887069 \"Role of vesicle tethering factors in the ER-Golgi membrane traffic.\"\n+\n+This review supports the core biological meaning of the requested term: tethering factors act before fusion and mediate initial attachment of vesicle carriers to target membranes.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:19887069 \"A well-accepted role for tethering factors is the initial attachment of transport carriers to acceptor membranes prior to fusion.\"\n+    - Supports the definition language that tethering provides the first point of contact before docking/fusion.\n+    - Supports use of a vesicle-focused membrane adaptor/tethering activity term.\n+\n+## PMID:19575650 \"Tethering factors as organizers of intracellular vesicular traffic.\"\n+\n+This broader review supports the generality of vesicle tethering across intracellular trafficking pathways and is appropriate definition provenance for a pan-species GO molecular function term.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:19575650 \"Intracellular trafficking entails the budding, transport, tethering, and fusion of transport vesicles and other membrane carriers.\"\n+    - Supports the general vesicular-traffic framing for the new MF term.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:19575650 \"Here we review recent progress toward a mechanistic understanding of vesicle tethering.\"\n+    - Supports the term as a general vesicle tethering activity, not restricted to ER-Golgi traffic.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+## Issue 31863 design-pattern notes\n+\n+No dedicated DOSDP file for `membrane-membrane adaptor activity` descendants was found in this checkout under `src/patterns/`.\n+\n+Relevant ontology precedent in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`:\n+\n+- `GO:0140177 membrane-membrane adaptor activity` is the direct parent and establishes the adaptor-activity framing.\n+- `GO:0140443 mitochondrion-plasma membrane adaptor activity` uses `adaptor activity` in the primary label and includes tether-related exact synonyms.\n+- `GO:0160190 peroxisome-mitochondrion membrane tether activity` uses `tether activity` as the primary label under the same parent.\n+- `GO:0160321 vesicle docking activity` is a sibling vesicle-targeting MF term and explicitly places docking after tethering.\n+\n+Design decision used here:\n+\n+- Do not add `intersection_of` axioms. There is no clear documented pattern in this checkout, and the requested term is adequately represented with an asserted `is_a` to `GO:0140177` plus a text definition.\n+- Keep the existing primary label `vesicle membrane tethering activity`, matching the issue request and current ontology content.\n+- Add `vesicle membrane adaptor activity` as an exact synonym so the term also aligns lexically with the parent's adaptor-activity naming scheme.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nM terms/GO_7770062.obo\nA RESEARCH.md\nA DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_7770062.obo\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_7770062.obo\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-a