acellular vesicular traffic.\"\n+\n+This broader review supports the generality of vesicle tethering across intracellular trafficking pathways and is appropriate definition provenance for a pan-species GO molecular function term.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:19575650 \"Intracellular trafficking entails the budding, transport, tethering, and fusion of transport vesicles and other membrane carriers.\"\n+    - Supports the general vesicular-traffic framing for the new MF term.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:19575650 \"Here we review recent progress toward a mechanistic understanding of vesicle tethering.\"\n+    - Supports the term as a general vesicle tethering activity, not restricted to ER-Golgi traffic.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,16 @@\n+## Issue 31863 design-pattern notes\n+\n+No dedicated DOSDP file for `membrane-membrane adaptor activity` descendants was found in this checkout under `src/patterns/`.\n+\n+Relevant ontology precedent in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`:\n+\n+- `GO:0140177 membrane-membrane adaptor activity` is the direct parent and establishes the adaptor-activity framing.\n+- `GO:0140443 mitochondrion-plasma membrane adaptor activity` uses `adaptor activity` in the primary label and includes tether-related exact synonyms.\n+- `GO:0160190 peroxisome-mitochondrion membrane tether activity` uses `tether activity` as the primary label under the same parent.\n+- `GO:0160321 vesicle docking activity` is a sibling vesicle-targeting MF term and explicitly places docking after tethering.\n+\n+Design decision used here:\n+\n+- Do not add `intersection_of` axioms. There is no clear documented pattern in this checkout, and the requested term is adequately represented with an asserted `is_a` to `GO:0140177` plus a text definition.\n+